{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]I’m alone with all my sorrow
[F]It’s so hard to face [C]tomorrow
[D7]Cause I knocked and no one met me at the [G7]door
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
I have asked the next door neighbor
[F]What you’ve packed and went away [C]for
[G7]But they only say you don’t live [C]here no [C7]more
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]When I sailed across the blue
[C]I thought I could count on you
[D7]But I’ve come back home sweetheart to find you [G7]gone
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[C]It’s a shame you couldn’t be here
[F]What a sorry sight to see [C]here
[G7]When a soldier knocks and finds nobody [C]home
{end_of_verse}

